# blog.folkol.com

https://jekyllrb.com/docs/usage/

## build
gem install bundle
bundle config set --local path 'vendor/bundle'
bundle install
bundle exec jekyll serve --livereload

## deploy
$ bundle exec jekyll clean
$ JEKYLL_ENV=production bundle exec jekyll build
$ aws-vault exec admin -- aws s3 sync _site/ s3://com.folkol.blog/ \
  --exclude "*" \
  --include "assets/*" \
  --include "images/*" \
  --cache-control "public,max-age=31536000,immutable"
$ aws-vault exec admin -- aws s3 sync _site/ s3://com.folkol.blog/ \
  --delete \
  --exclude "assets/*" --exclude "images/*" \
  --cache-control "public,max-age=300"

## notes audit tool

The `bin/notes-audit` tool helps triage files in `~/Documents/notes` as potential blog post candidates.

### Usage

```bash
# Review pending notes (default command)
./bin/notes-audit review

# Show statistics
./bin/notes-audit status

# Reset decisions
./bin/notes-audit reset --all              # Reset all decisions
./bin/notes-audit reset --path /path/to/note  # Reset specific note

# Clear rejection for a note
./bin/notes-audit unreject --path /path/to/note

# List accepted or rejected notes
./bin/notes-audit list accepted
./bin/notes-audit list rejected
```

### How it works

- Scans `~/Documents/notes` recursively for text-like files
- Shows a summary and opens each file in `less` for review
- After viewing, you can: accept (copy to `candidates/`), reject, postpone, or skip
- Accepted notes are copied to `candidates/` with a date prefix (unless already present)
- Rejected notes are marked and won't appear again unless updated
- Updated notes automatically re-enter the queue
- State is persisted in `.notes-audit/` (excluded from Jekyll)
